=Bio=

"Prashant Varma is Coordinator of the Deerpark Institute, Bir, India. Deerpark was founded by the Ven. Khyentshe Norbu Rinpoche a prominent Buddhist monk from Bhutan, known from his films including “The Cup”. Prashant made Deerpark Institute a lively place attracting many Young Indian people, as well as from all over the world, meeting with Buddhism in an artistic setting, even though its isolated location in the Himalayas. Prashant is active in the International Network of Engaged Buddhists."


